Measured by client-wise test dataset-based micro accuracy and macro F1-score, WeCFL outperforms almost all baselines on Fashion-MNIST and CIFAR-10 datasets. IFCA also doesnâ€™t show a very competitive performance on both two datasets. One of the main reasons is due to IFCAâ€™s unstable clustering capability. IFCAâ€™s clustering procedure is not a usual clustering algorithm with a well-defined distance or similarity metric. Specifically, in IFCAâ€™s clustering procedure, the similarity metric is based on how the cluster-specific model performs on the clientâ€™s local dataset. This kind of metric is unlike other classic distance and similarity metrics which have demonstrated good characteristics from geometry and algebra perspectives.
